One person sustained minor injuries following a serious collision on the corner of Shamrock and Pretoria Roads in Primrose on Thursday. On arrival EMER-G-MED paramedics found that a car had been T-boned by a bakkie at a high-speed, leaving the car severely damaged. &#8220;Despite the horrific mechanism, the driver escaped with only minor injuries. The driver of the bakkie was assessed and found to have sustained no injuries&#8221;, said Max Cohen. The patient were transported by provincial services to a nearby hospital for further treatment. The cause of the incident is still unknown as the case is being investigated by local traffic authorities.&nbsp;-TNA Reporter